{{Infobox French commune |name = Le Grand-Pressigny |commune status = [[Communes of France|Commune]] |image = Grand Pressigny- L'église.jpg |caption = The church in Le Grand-Pressigny |image coat of arms = Blason ville fr Le Grand-Pressigny (Indre-et-Loire).svg |region = Centre |department = Indre-et-Loire |arrondissement = Loches |canton = Descartes |intercommunality = [[Communauté de communes Loches Sud Touraine|CC Loches Sud Touraine]] |mayor = François-Nicolas Joannès |term = 2008&ndash;2014 |coordinates = {{coord|46.9211|0.8036|format=dms|display=inline,title}} |elevation m = 60 |elevation min m = 52 |elevation max m = 135 |area km2 = 39.55 |population = 1012 |population date = 2009 |INSEE = 37113 |postal code = 37350 }}
'''Le Grand-Pressigny''' is a [[Communes of France|commune]] in the [[Indre-et-Loire]] [[Departments of France|department]] in central [[France]].
There is a [[Chalcolithic]] [[flint]] mine located in the commune. It produced an unusual caramel-coloured stone which appears to have been highly prized across Europe with examples found in the [[Pyrenees]], the [[Netherlands]] and [[Switzerland]]. Blocks of flint and unfinished [[Lithic reduction#Blank|blanks]] were traded, as well as finished tools.
