===Anime===
An anime television series was announced on June 21, 2014.<ref name="AnimeAnnouncement">{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-06-21/gakko-gurashi-survival-manga-gets-tv-anime/.75791 |title=Gakkō Gurashi! Survival Manga Gets TV Anime |website=[[Anime News Network]] |date=June 21, 2014 |accessdate=June 22, 2014}}</ref> The series was directed by Masaomi Ando at [[Lerche (studio)|Lerche]], with scripts by manga writer Norimitsu Kaihō and character design by Haruko Iikuza. The series aired in Japan between July 9, 2015 and September 24, 2015 and was simulcast by [[Crunchyroll]].<ref name="debut">{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-02-23/gakko-gurashi-zombie-anime-cast-lerche-staff-summer-debut-revealed/.85295 |title=Gakkō Gurashi! Zombie Anime's Cast, Lerche Staff, Summer Debut Revealed |website=[[Anime News Network]] |date=February 23, 2015 |accessdate=April 18, 2015 }}</ref><ref name="Ai Kayano">{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-05-22/ai-kayano-joins-school-live-gakko-gurashi-anime-cast/.88440 |title=Ai Kayano Joins School-Live/Gakkō Gurashi! Anime's Cast |date=May 22, 2015 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=July 5, 2015 }}</ref><ref name="Crunchyroll">{{cite web |url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2015/07/08-1/crunchyroll-adds-school-live-anime-plus-four-new-motion-manga |title=Crunchyroll Adds "SCHOOL-LIVE!" Anime, Plus Four New Motion Manga |last=Marcias |first=Patrick |date=July 8, 2015 |website=[[Crunchyroll]] |accessdate=July 9, 2015 }}</ref> The series features four pieces of theme music; one opening theme and three ending themes. The opening theme is {{nihongo|"Friend Shitai"|ふ・れ・ん・ど・し・た・い|Furendo Shitai|"I Want To Be Friends"}} by Gakuen Seikatsu-bu ([[Inori Minase]], [[Ari Ozawa]], [[Mao Ichimichi|M.A.O]], and [[Rie Takahashi]]). The ending theme is {{nihongo|"Harmonize Clover"|ハーモナイズ・クローバー|Hāmonaizu Kurōbā}} by [[Maon Kurosaki]] for episodes 1-3, 5, and 9,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-06-23/maon-kurosaki-sings-school-live-gakko-gurashi-ending-theme/.89588 |title=Maon Kurosaki Sings School-Live/Gakkō Gurashi! Ending Theme |date=June 23, 2015 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=July 5, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2015-06-23/gakko-gurashi-voice-actresses-sing-op-theme-in-music-video-preview/.89616 |title=Gakkō Gurashi! Voice Actresses Sing OP Theme in Music Video Preview |last=Lamb |first=Lynzee |date=June 23, 2015 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=July 5, 2015 }}</ref> "We took each other's hand" by Kaori Sawada for episode 4, and {{nihongo|"Afterglow"|アフターグロー|Afutāgurō}} by Kurosaki for episode 6-8 and 10-11. The series was licensed in North America by [[Sentai Filmworks]] and released on Blu-ray and DVD with an English dub on June 27, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-07-02/sentai-filmworks-acquires-ushio-and-tora-gate-school-live-wakaba-girl-aoharu-x-machinegun-anime/.89985 |title=Sentai Filmworks Acquires Ushio & Tora, Gate, School Live, Wakaba Girl, Aoharu X Machinegun Anime |date=July 2, 2015 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=July 2, 2015 }}</ref> A drama-CD based on the anime television series was released at [[Comiket]] 88 on August 14, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gakkougurashi.com/news/index00530000.html|title=コミックマーケット88 グッズ情報を公開いたしました！ -TVアニメ「がっこうぐらし！」公式サイト-|language=Japanese|accessdate=August 20, 2015}}</ref>

